  "text": "Here we model the effect of the cumulative sum of the repeated binary measures on the time to event or censoring. Let . The joint distribution of Q and Y can be expressed as a mixture, where f(Q, Y|Z) = f(Q|Ỹ, Z) f(Y|Z). Let the probability of having a time to event in or before category k, given the cumulative sum of repeated measures Ỹ i , and covariate vector Z i be defined by [CITATION_1] and .",
